parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front differential can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Grinding or whining noise from the front of the vehicle
loud squealing noise
wheels locking up
vehicle rolling away on an incline
loss of traction
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Whining or humming noise from the rear of the vehicle
oil leaks from the rear differential
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and engine components can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle rolling forward while the brake pedal is engaged
and fault codes on the module requiring an upgrade.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Tire blowout
and uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the traction system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle shutting down on slight incline
and traction system engaging unnecessarily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column lock can cause the steering wheel to lock, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks
the key will not turn in the ignition
the steering wheel is stuck in an upward position
the vehicle will not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the steering wheel to shake uncontrollably, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes uncontrollably
loud grinding or knocking noise from the steering column
the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to bounce erratically, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle bounces erratically
the front end of the vehicle collapses while parked
excessive strain on ball joints and front control arms.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the differential can cause loud humming sounds, making it difficult to drive the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Loud humming sounds from the differential.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light is on
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the passenger side airbag on the dashboard is prematurely splitting
the dashboard has cracks around the airbag system
the front dash has cracked all the way across
the seat belt warning light does not illuminate when the seat belt is not being utilized
the airbag warning light illuminates intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard around the airbag system can lead to the airbag not deploying properly in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The dashboard has cracks around the airbag system
the front dash has cracked all the way across
the passenger side airbag on the dashboard is prematurely splitting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger occupancy sensor can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag fault light is illuminated
the airbag will not deploy in an accident
the sensor intermittently works.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the vehicle cuts off without warning
the parking brake warning light comes on when starting the car and putting it in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to go into limp mode, making it difficult or impossible to drive, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into limp mode
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause a loud abnormal noise, vibrations, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: A loud abnormal noise is heard coming from the rear of the vehicle
the vehicle vibrates while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension can cause the vehicle to drop to the ground, making it difficult or impossible to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's suspension drops to the ground
the vehicle lowers or rises without the suspension switch being activated
the suspension fault light displays.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause various issues, including warning indicators illuminating on the instrument panel, loss of power, and failure of electrical components, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Warning indicators illuminate on the instrument panel
loss of power
failure of electrical components
battery drain
and random error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Power and Fuel Level Sensor Electrical Connector Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump power and fuel level sensor electrical connector can cause the fuel pump to fail, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Fuel pump failure
engine stalling
loss of power
and overheating of the connector.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sunroof drain tube can cause water to accumulate in the passenger side floor, leading to electrical damage and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the passenger side floor
electrical damage
and failure of electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless entry system can cause the doors to lock and prevent occupants from exiting the vehicle, which can lead to safety risks.
symptoms: Doors lock and prevent occupants from exiting the vehicle
and the only way to unlock the doors is by using the keyless entry.
